flavor_text_entries.ruby:
SABLEYE lead quiet lives deep inside
caverns. They are feared, however,
because these POKéMON are thought to steal the spirits of people when their
eyes burn with a sinister glow in the
darkness.
flavor_text_entries.sapphire:
SABLEYE digs the ground with sharpened
claws to find rocks that it eats.
Substances in the eaten rocks crystallize and rise up to the POKéMON’s
body surface.
flavor_text_entries.emerald:
It digs branching holes in caves using its
sharp claws in search of food--raw gems.
A SABLEYE lurks in darkness and is seen
only rarely.
flavor_text_entries.firered:
It feeds on gemstone crystals.
In darkness, its eyes sparkle with the
glitter of jewels.

flavor_text_entries.diamond:

flavor_text_entries.alpha-sapphire:

flavor_text_entries.sun:
It’s a fiend for gemstones, so it stalks Carbink.
Unfortunately, Gabite almost always grabs
them first.
flavor_text_entries.moon:
This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes
begin to glow with a sinister shine, it’s believed
that Sableye will steal people’s spirits away.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-sun:
It digs through the ground with its hard claws
and crunches down gems with its thick pointy
teeth. Carbink is its favorite food.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-moon:
Materials from gems it has eaten float to the
surface of its body and can form an infinite
number of patterns among individuals.
